						<div class="postbody">Thanks for the reply.  Since nobody answered in good time, I bit the bullet and did some research, checking out examples in BASIC and C.  After a bit of thinking and coding, I made up a nice working Mandelbrot generator in 6502 ASM.  But sorry NES fans, my program is for the 7.16 Mhz PC-Engine, because the NES' CPU just isn't fast enough to render some nice fractals without my falling asleep...  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":-)" title="Smile" />
<br />
<br />I'll update this post when I've finished up the PCE program, since somebody might be interested.</div>

					
