				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The Mandelbrot and Julia sets use the same formula, but they use C differently.
<br />
<br />The Mandelbrot set use the current complex number (where the pixel coordinates are) for the value of C on every iteration, thus it changes on every pixel.
<br />
<br />Julia sets use one fixed complex number for the value of C on every iteration, thus it remains fixed.  The fixed complex number is supposed to be assigned before rendering the Julia set.
<br />
<br />Since Julia sets use a fixed point and the Mandelbrot set uses every point, it can be said that the Mandelbrot set is an index to every possible Julia set.  I will even go so far as to say the Mandelbrot set *is* every Julia set mashed up together in one fractal universe.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Be whatever the situation demands.</div>
