					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">doppelganger wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Since Julia sets use a fixed point and the Mandelbrot set uses every point, it can be said that the Mandelbrot set is an index to every possible Julia set.  I will even go so far as to say the Mandelbrot set *is* every Julia set mashed up together in one fractal universe.</div>
<br />You'd be correct. The Mandelbrot set was invented as a way to test conjectures about the set of Julia sets. Wikipedia <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mandelbrot_set#Formal_definition" class="postlink">states</a> that "it is the subset of the complex plane consisting of those parameters c for which the Julia set of fc is connected."</div>

